&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT US:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Talon.One is the most powerful incentives engine that unifies loyalty, promotions and gamification into one holistic platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Backed by enterprise-grade security and scalability, Talon.One empowers companies to build personalized, profitable promotions and loyalty programs using any data. Today, over 250 of the world’s most-loved brands including Adidas, Sephora and Carlsberg work with Talon.One to drive deeper engagement and lasting loyalty with their customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Customer Success Manager at Talon.One, you&#39;ll be part of a dynamic Post Sales team consisting of Customer Success Managers, Technical Account Managers and Solution Architects. We foster a collaborative environment and alignment with various internal stakeholders in Sales, Partnerships, Product, and Marketing. We prioritize strong collaboration, open communication, and mentoring to promote bi-directional growth. Talon.One is committed to creating an inclusive workplace, as we believe it is essential for both ethical reasons and to positively influence the tech industry as a whole.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Building on strong performance this year, our team is expanding and we’re hiring a Customer Success Manager, APAC to support our rapid growth in Australia and our rapidly growing team in the APAC region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Customer Success Manager, you&#39;ll build strong relationships to drive product adoption and turn customer insights into actionable feedback. You&#39;ll connect customers&#39; marketing goals with our API-driven product, troubleshoot issues with our tech team, and design scalable success processes. Your communication skills will help enhance our enterprise solutions and streamline project management.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a remote position with a requirement to be based in Australia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ONCE YOU ARE HERE YOU WILL:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with customers to understand their goals and pains, drive adoption, and translate that into actionable insights for our Sales, Marketing, and Product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect customers’ marketing objectives with our technical, API-driven product and clearly explain complex product configuration steps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with technical operations (Customer Integration Engineer) and the development team to integrate Talon.One and troubleshoot technical issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate at both one-to-many and one-on-one levels, across role types (tech/marketing), organization level, and cultures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document and share important information about our Customers to keep a clear internal record, build training resources, and reduce support tickets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive retention and growth to your book of business, handling upsell and renewal conversations with a book of business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and deliver strategic and business value to customers daily&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT TALON.ONE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Talon.One is the most powerful incentives engine that unifies loyalty, promotions and gamification into one holistic platform.&amp;nbsp;Backed by enterprise-grade security and scalability, Talon.One empowers companies to build personalized, profitable promotions and loyalty programs using any data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, over 250 of the world’s most-loved brands including Adidas, Sephora and Carlsberg work with Talon.One to drive deeper engagement and lasting loyalty with their customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Data Analyst, you will be responsible for all kinds of analysis within the company. You will be in close cooperation with the stakeholders from all departments (Marketing, Product, Customer Success, Sales, Management, GTM etc.), helping us define their KPIs and come up with data use cases that will help the business in all its operations. You will be at the forefront of all synergies between the business and the rest of the data team by aligning on the data strategy, specifying use cases and KPIs, writing requests for the data engineers, etc. Based on the data warehouse models, you will be responsible for advanced analytics and reporting that you will deliver to the whole company. Your main focus will be Product and Customer Success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ONCE YOU ARE HERE YOU WILL:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve business processes and empower the stakeholders to make better decisions by defining KPIs and coming up with analysis ideas that would benefit the departments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the connector between the business stakeholders and the data team: align on data strategy, define business use cases, work with the data engineers to grow the DWH, and improve the models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create advanced analysis on Looker (or other tools like Google Colab for Python analysis), deliver them to the stakeholders, maintain them, and ensure they are being used the right way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the owner of the Looker models, test them, and make them grow by developing new measures, dimensions, and business logic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across all departments to enable self-service analytics, improve the reporting in place, develop automated processes, and specify new business use cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be at the centre of a freshly built modern data stack, can make it grow, and learn new skills and technologies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Data Engineers on the continuous development of our Data Warehouse, directly contributing to data validation and quality assurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE NEED YOU TO BRING TO THE TABLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+&amp;nbsp; years of experience in the field of data analytics, ideally with some B2B SaaS experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced experience with dashboarding tools (Looker, Tableau, PowerBI, Metabase etc.), knowledge of how to design, build, and maintain a data model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with SQL. BigQuery, DBT, Python, Looker are a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of business analytics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are&amp;nbsp; curious and passionate about data, and would like to widen your knowledge of the modern data stack and learn new skills and technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in collaboration with stakeholders and translating business requirements into data specifications, dashboards,&amp;nbsp; automated processes, especially in the field of Product, Customer Success, Marketing, and Tech departments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactiveness to carry out advanced analysis towards better and busin

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT TALON.ONE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Talon.One is the most powerful incentives engine that unifies loyalty, promotions and gamification into one holistic platform.&amp;nbsp;Backed by enterprise-grade security and scalability, Talon.One empowers companies to build personalized, profitable promotions and loyalty programs using any data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, over 250 of the world’s most-loved brands including Adidas, Sephora and Carlsberg work with Talon.One to drive deeper engagement and lasting loyalty with their customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Talon.One’s R&amp;amp;D has a cross-functional group of engineers, product thinkers, and designers who build and scale the systems behind Talon.One’s platform. Each team owns a clear slice of our ecosystem, operating with autonomy and shared accountability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Platform Tribe, the Infrastructure team focuses on the foundations that power everything we build: Cloud Architecture, Kubernetes, Networking, Terraform, CI/CD, GitOps, and more. We design scalable, reliable, and secure systems so product engineers can move fast with confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value curiosity, open collaboration, and mutual growth. Everyone has visibility into how things work end to end, and we encourage mentoring and knowledge sharing across disciplines. Talon.One is building an inclusive workplace where diverse perspectives shape better systems and better outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re based in Berlin and welcome professionals already here or excited to relocate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Senior DevOps Engineer to join our Platform Tribe. You’ll help evolve the systems that keep Talon.One reliable, secure, and scalable. Our team uses a Kanban flow and a quarterly roadmap that balances long-term initiatives and iterative improvements. You’ll collaborate closely with infrastructure, platform, and product engineers to build resilient infrastructure, automate operations, and simplify cloud complexity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value engineers who take ownership, bring proactive thinking to design discussions, and share knowledge openly. This is a hands-on role where reliability, automation, and thoughtful collaboration define success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE NEED YOU TO BRING TO THE TABLE:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in a Cloud Infrastructure or DevOps Engineering role, with a strong record of building and maintaining production systems at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of CI/CD pipelines, with hands-on experience improving automation, reliability, and developer workflows, ideally using tools like ArgoCD or similar GitOps-based deployment systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert knowledge of Docker and Kubernetes, including best practices for observability, scalability, and resilience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid experience with cloud providers (preferably GCP) and a sound grasp of cloud-native architectures and infrastructure as code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with parts of our stack: Bash, Golang, PostgreSQL, and Git.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Datadog or Prometheus for monitoring and metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High levels of ownership and autonomy, you execute independently, make pragmatic decisions, and follow through with consistency and care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine interest in mentoring others, sharing context, and raising the technical bar of the team through collaboration and knowledge transfer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR TECHNOLOGY:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT TALON.ONE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Talon.One is the most powerful incentives engine that unifies loyalty, promotions and gamification into one holistic platform.&amp;nbsp;Backed by enterprise-grade security and scalability, Talon.One empowers companies to build personalized, profitable promotions and loyalty programs using any data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, over 250 of the world’s most-loved brands including Adidas, Sephora and Carlsberg work with Talon.One to drive deeper engagement and lasting loyalty with their customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leading the Enterprise sales team for the Americas at Talon.One, you’ll play a mission-critical role in driving new business in-region by selling the world’s most flexible promotions and loyalty platform to top-tier brands. You’ll be selling a composable, API-first solution that integrates with partners like Shopify, Braze, Salesforce, Segment, and other best-of-breed players in the marketing and commerce tech stacks. We’re looking for strategic leaders with initiative, intellectual curiosity, and ownership. Your sellers will own the full sales cycle - from outbounding to discovery through closing - selling into complex organizations, both technical and business audiences, C-suites, and brands that want to transform the way they incentivize their customers. If you enjoy working with and coaching high-performing sellers to achieve their highest potential - then this role is the right opportunity for you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a remote role, and while we prefer candidates to be located within commuting distance of one of our hubs (Boston or New York City), it’s not required. However you must be comfortable working Eastern or Central Time Zone hours. This role also requires occasional domestic and international travel (&amp;lt;50% of the time).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead our growing Enterprise Sales team in AMER, which is an integral part of our 20+ person global sales function. The Enterprise sales team currently consists of 3 sellers, covering all business outside of the Named Large Enterprise Accounts. Our mission is to drive revenue by delivering measurable value to enterprise clients through highly personalized, technically robust solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the AMER Sales team, you’ll report to the VP Sales, AMER and collaborate closely with Sales Engineers, Customer Success, and Marketing to build meaningful client relationships and close complex deals. This integrated approach ensures a seamless customer experience throughout the entire sales cycle. We are a global team of self-starters who thrive on accountability and mutual success. Our culture emphasizes cross-functional collaboration, data-driven strategies, and a customer-centric mindset, all aimed at delivering exceptional value to our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ONCE YOU ARE HERE YOU WILL:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and execute on the enterprise revenue targets within the AMER region, aligning your team&#39;s execution with overarching global objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and lead a high-performing sales team: recruit, onboard, coach, and develop a team of Enterprise Account Executives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a culture of success, accountability, and continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and continuously refine processes for predictable pipeline generation, accurate forecasting, and efficient deal closure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with marketing, partnerships, and customer success to create integrated campaigns and enable land-and-expand strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for the

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT TALON.ONE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Talon.One is the most powerful incentives engine that unifies loyalty, promotions and gamification into one holistic platform.&amp;nbsp;Backed by enterprise-grade security and scalability, Talon.One empowers companies to build personalized, profitable promotions and loyalty programs using any data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, over 250 of the world’s most-loved brands including Adidas, Sephora and Carlsberg work with Talon.One to drive deeper engagement and lasting loyalty with their customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our development team consists of specialists in frontend, backend, QA, product, and more. We work in small cross-functional teams that give everybody insight and hands-on experience of what everyone else is doing. Each team is self-sustained, autonomous, and responsible for a specific product area in our platform. We believe strongly in opening opportunities for developers to be mentored and grow their skills. We are working to make Talon.One an inclusive workplace, as we believe it is the right thing to do and we want to have a positive impact on the entire tech industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Frontend developer to join our team and bring their FE expertise to the table.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that, due to proximity to the team, we are looking for professionals located in Berlin.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ONCE YOU ARE HERE YOU WILL:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a small cross-functional team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the visual and functional designs at the heart of our ReactJS web application&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review others&#39; code and ensure that quality standards are maintained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise team members in their day-to-day coding tasks as well as with overall architectural decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with our UX team to improve the user experience and interface of our product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cooperate with the team and customer representatives to plan projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor others, both junior developers on their learning paths and more experienced developers who are interested in learning about new fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE NEED YOU TO BRING TO THE TABLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Founded experience with modern web technologies (e.g. React, Vue.js, Angular)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding REST APIs, and a passion for typed Javascript code (e.g. Typescript, Flow)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in rich and friendly User Experience and Interfaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive attitude in improving the product, the team, its processes and our code base&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A full-stack attitude. Everybody has their strengths, but no piece of the project stands alone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team-first attitude; As a group we strive to leave egos at home&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Big-picture thinking: You collaborate with non-developers to clarify requirements and help plan projects, with an eye on the overall impact to the business &amp;amp; product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to contribute to an inclusive and diverse team and foster open communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empathy for your colleagues and your customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TECHNOLOGY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TypeScript, React, Redux and CSS modules for our web application&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Google Cloud Platform (Container Engine)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PostgreSQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go for our API &amp;amp; rule engine (&quot;golang&quot; for the search engines)&lt;/li&gt;

